TITLE: Implementing Counter Contract Logic in Sway
DESCRIPTION: Implementation of the Counter contract that manages a count value in storage. The contract initializes a count with zero and provides methods to increment and decrement the count by one, as well as return the current value.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FuelLabs/sway/blob/master/docs/reference/src/documentation/examples/counter.md#2025-04-17_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: sway
CODE:
```
storage {
    count: u64 = 0,
}

impl Counter for Contract {
    #[storage(read, write)]
    fn increment() {
        storage.count = storage.count + 1;
    }

    #[storage(read, write)]
    fn decrement() {
        storage.count = storage.count - 1;
    }

    #[storage(read)]
    fn count() -> u64 {
        storage.count
    }
}
```

