TITLE: Struct Instantiation in Sway
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates three different ways to instantiate structs: hardcoding values, using different variable names, and shorthand notation with matching field names.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FuelLabs/sway/blob/master/docs/book/src/basics/structs_tuples_and_enums.md#2025-04-17_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: sway
CODE:
```
fn main() {
    // Method 1: Hardcoding the values
    let foo1 = Foo {
        bar: 42,
        baz: true,
    };

    // Method 2: Using variables with different names
    let number = 42;
    let boolean = true;
    let foo2 = Foo {
        bar: number,
        baz: boolean,
    };

    // Method 3: Using variables with the same name as fields
    let bar = 42;
    let baz = true;
    let foo3 = Foo { bar, baz };
}
```

