TITLE: Basic Contract Call Implementation in Sway
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates a basic contract-to-contract call setup with two contracts: ContractA defines a receivable interface, while ContractB implements the calling functionality.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FuelLabs/sway/blob/master/docs/book/src/blockchain-development/calling_contracts.md#2025-04-17_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: sway
CODE:
```
// ./contract_a.sw
contract;

abi ContractA {
    fn receive(field_1: bool, field_2: u64) -> u64;
}

impl ContractA for Contract {
    fn receive(field_1: bool, field_2: u64) -> u64 {
        assert(field_1 == true);
        assert(field_2 > 0);
        return_45()
    }
}

fn return_45() -> u64 {
  45
}
```

LANGUAGE: sway
CODE:
```
// ./contract_b.sw
contract;

use contract_a::ContractA;

abi ContractB {
    fn make_call();
}

const contract_id = 0x79fa8779bed2f36c3581d01c79df8da45eee09fac1fd76a5a656e16326317ef0;

impl ContractB for Contract {
    fn make_call() {
      let x = abi(ContractA, contract_id);
      let return_value = x.receive(true, 3); // will be 45
    }
}
```

