TITLE: Implementing remove_liquidity Function in Sway
DESCRIPTION: This function removes liquidity from the pool by burning liquidity tokens and returning a proportional amount of both tokens to the user.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FuelLabs/sway/blob/master/docs/reference/src/documentation/examples/liquidity-pool.md#2025-04-17_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: Sway
CODE:
```
fn remove_liquidity(pool: LiquidityPool, liquidity_amount: u64) -> (LiquidityPool, u64, u64) {
    let token1_amount = (liquidity_amount * pool.token1_balance) / pool.liquidity_tokens;
    let token2_amount = (liquidity_amount * pool.token2_balance) / pool.liquidity_tokens;

    LiquidityPool {
        token1_balance: pool.token1_balance - token1_amount,
        token2_balance: pool.token2_balance - token2_amount,
        liquidity_tokens: pool.liquidity_tokens - liquidity_amount,
    },
    token1_amount,
    token2_amount
}
```

