TITLE: Implementing add_liquidity Function in Sway
DESCRIPTION: This function adds liquidity to the pool by depositing both tokens. It calculates the amount of liquidity tokens to mint based on the deposits and current pool state.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FuelLabs/sway/blob/master/docs/reference/src/documentation/examples/liquidity-pool.md#2025-04-17_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: Sway
CODE:
```
fn add_liquidity(pool: LiquidityPool, token1_amount: u64, token2_amount: u64) -> (LiquidityPool, u64) {
    let liquidity_minted: u64;
    if pool.liquidity_tokens == 0 {
        liquidity_minted = token1_amount;
    } else {
        let token1_fraction = (token1_amount * pool.liquidity_tokens) / pool.token1_balance;
        let token2_fraction = (token2_amount * pool.liquidity_tokens) / pool.token2_balance;
        liquidity_minted = min(token1_fraction, token2_fraction);
    }

    LiquidityPool {
        token1_balance: pool.token1_balance + token1_amount,
        token2_balance: pool.token2_balance + token2_amount,
        liquidity_tokens: pool.liquidity_tokens + liquidity_minted,
    },
    liquidity_minted
}
```

