TITLE: Defining a Smart Contract ABI in Sway
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows how to define an Application Binary Interface (ABI) for a wallet contract. The ABI declares the external functions that can be called, including storage interactions and documentation comments.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FuelLabs/sway/blob/master/docs/reference/src/documentation/language/program-types/contract.md#2025-04-17_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: sway
CODE:
```
abi Wallet {
    /// By using `#[storage(read)]` we tell the compiler that this function
    /// only needs read access to storage which is useful for gas estimation.
    #[storage(read)]
    fn get_balance() -> u64;

    /// By using `#[storage(write)]` we tell the compiler that this function
    /// modifies the contracts storage
    #[storage(write)]
    fn receive_funds();

    /// We can use a combination of annotations if needed
    #[storage(read, write)]
    fn send_funds(amount_to_send: u64, recipient_address: Identity);
}
```

