TITLE: Simple Pattern Matching in Sway
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates basic pattern matching in Sway where different integer values are matched against patterns, with the result assigned to a variable. Each arm returns a different multiple of 10 based on the matched value, with a catch-all case handling unmatched values.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FuelLabs/sway/blob/master/docs/reference/src/documentation/language/control-flow/match/single-line.md#2025-04-17_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: sway
CODE:
```
fn simple_match(input: u64) -> u64 {
    // With match expressions we can match our parameter to a specific variable.
    let mult = match input {
        0 => 0,
        1 => 10,
        2 => 20,
        3 => 30,
        4 => 40,
        5 | 10 => 50,
        _ => 999,
    };

    mult
}
```

