TITLE: Example of Using Call Data in a Sway Contract
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to match on the function selector in a Sway contract. It extracts the first four bytes from the call data to determine which function is being called.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FuelLabs/sway/blob/master/docs/reference/src/documentation/language/call-data/index.md#2025-04-17_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: sway
CODE:
```
fn main() -> bool {
    // Extract the first four bytes from the call data
    let selector = asm(r1, r2, r3) {
        mir_call_data r1;
        lw r2 r1 i0;
        and r3 r2 0xFFFFFFFF;
        r3: u32
    };

    // Match the function selector
    match selector {
        0x0000000a => do_something(),
        0x0000000b => do_something_else(),
        _ => revert(0),
    }
}
```

