TITLE: Using Option<T> for Handling Invalid Operations in Sway
DESCRIPTION: Example of using Option<T> to handle potentially invalid operations, specifically division by zero. The function returns Some with the result if valid, or None if division by zero is attempted.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FuelLabs/sway/blob/master/docs/book/src/basics/commonly_used_library_types.md#2025-04-17_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: sway
CODE:
```
use std::option::Option;

fn divide(dividend: u64, divisor: u64) -> Option<u64> {
    if divisor == 0 {
        Option::None
    } else {
        Option::Some(dividend / divisor)
    }
}

fn main() -> u64 {
    let result = divide(10, 2);
    match result {
        Option::Some(value) => value,
        Option::None => 0,
    }
}
```

