TITLE: Using ref mut with Complex Data Types in Sway Functions
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use 'ref mut' with more complex data types such as tuples and enums. It includes functions for modifying tuple and enum values, along with example usage.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FuelLabs/sway/blob/master/docs/book/src/basics/functions.md#2025-04-17_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: sway
CODE:
```
fn modify_tuple(ref mut tuple: (u64, u64)) {
    tuple.0 += 1;
    tuple.1 += 1;
}

enum Number {
    One: u64,
    Two: u64,
}

fn modify_enum(ref mut num: Number) {
    match num {
        Number::One(ref mut n) => { *n += 1 },
        Number::Two(ref mut n) => { *n += 2 },
    }
}
```

LANGUAGE: sway
CODE:
```
fn main() {
    let mut tuple = (0, 0);
    modify_tuple(tuple);
    assert(tuple.0 == 1 && tuple.1 == 1);

    let mut num = Number::One(0);
    modify_enum(num);
    match num {
        Number::One(n) => assert(n == 1),
        _ => revert(0),
    }
}
```

