TITLE: Implementing Fizzbuzz Logic Function in Sway
DESCRIPTION: This function takes a u64 input and returns a State enum based on the Fizzbuzz rules. It checks divisibility by 3 and 5, returning the appropriate State variant accordingly.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FuelLabs/sway/blob/master/docs/reference/src/documentation/examples/fizzbuzz.md#2025-04-17_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: sway
CODE:
```
fn fizzbuzz(input: u64) -> State {
    if input % 15 == 0 {
        State::Fizzbuzz
    } else if input % 3 == 0 {
        State::Fizz
    } else if input % 5 == 0 {
        State::Buzz
    } else {
        State::Number(input)
    }
}
```

