TITLE: Using Shortened Names for Intermediate Variables in Sway
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to use intermediate variables with shorter names to improve readability when dealing with multiple levels of indentation or verbose names.
SOURCE: https://github.com/FuelLabs/sway/blob/master/docs/reference/src/documentation/language/style-guide/intermediate-variables.md#2025-04-17_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: sway
CODE:
```
struct VeryLongNameThatDescribesTheObject {
    field: u64,
}

fn shortened_name(objects: Vec<VeryLongNameThatDescribesTheObject>) -> u64 {
    let mut sum = 0;

    // DO
    for object in objects.iter() {
        let o = object;
        if o.field > 5 {
            if o.field < 10 {
                sum += o.field;
            }
        }
    }

    // DON'T
    for object in objects.iter() {
        if object.field > 5 {
            if object.field < 10 {
                sum += object.field;
            }
        }
    }

    sum
}
```

